# v4.4.1 — Category display name in Travel Book (implementation)

Implements the first small presentation-model extraction from the v4.4.0 review.

| Item | Status |
|---|---|
| Release | v4.4.1 |
| Scope | `trip export-md` Daily schedule category line only |
| Validation fixture | [Okinawa Sesoko 2026 sample](../../samples/okinawa_sesoko_2026/README.md) |

## Goal

Daily schedule category lines use `ItineraryCategory::definition().display_name` instead of raw enum strings (`transport`, `hotel`, …).

This is a **presentation-oriented** change — not a Markdown-only mapping table.

## Rule

- When `ItineraryItem.category` is set, emit a detail line with:
  - Field label: `種別:` (consistent with other Japanese Travel Book field labels: `場所:`, `メモ:`)
  - Value: `category.definition().display_name` from domain (`移動`, `ホテル`, …)
- When category is unset, omit the line (unchanged).
- Domain enum values (`as_str()`) are unchanged.
- JSON export and SQLite schema unchanged.

## Code

- `src/io/markdown.rs`
  - `format_travel_book_category_detail_line` — reusable category detail line (presentation)
  - `format_itinerary_item_markdown` — calls helper instead of `category.as_str()`

## Tests

- `format_travel_book_category_detail_line` — Transport → `種別: 移動`; all categories use definition, not `as_str()`
- `test_export_md_includes_category` — Hotel → `種別: ホテル`
- `test_export_md_omits_category_when_unset` — no `種別:` line

## Regenerate Okinawa golden

```bash
bash samples/okinawa_sesoko_2026/seed.sh
